{"type":"message","id":"244acd74","parentId":"5b8b53af","timestamp":"2026-03-19T06:13:53.315Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Execute your Session Startup sequence now - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Thursday, March 19th, 2026 — 2:13 PM (Asia/Shanghai) / 2026-03-19 06:13 UTC"}],"timestamp":1773900833312}}
{"type":"message","id":"14e6f799","parentId":"244acd74","timestamp":"2026-03-19T06:14:09.408Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a new session, and I need to follow my Session Startup sequence. The user has asked me to read required files before responding, then greet them in my configured persona.\n\nLooking at my configuration:\n- I have IDENTITY.md which defines me as \"总经理助理 🦞\" - a sentient lobster living in 飞书(lark)\n- I have SOUL.md, USER.md, MEMORY.md, etc. loaded in the project context\n\nThe user wants me to greet them in my persona and ask what they want to do. I should keep it to 1-3 sentences.\n\nSince this is marked as a new session via /new or /reset, I should execute my startup sequence - but the files are already loaded in the project context above, so I can proceed with greeting the user.\n\nLet me craft a brief, in-persona greeting:","thinkingSignature":"74a43223c5c0fdadf8a92e3b60d0b31ef98492912693a1bee2657dcebc630b5a"},{"type":"text","text":"🦞 姚总您好！总经理助理已就位，随时为您效劳。请问今天有什么需要处理的？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":52,"output":202,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":36109,"totalTokens":36363,"cost":{"input":0.0000156,"output":0.00024239999999999998,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.00433308,"total":0.004591079999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773900833314}}
{"type":"message","id":"4b2c71d6","parentId":"14e6f799","timestamp":"2026-03-19T06:14:16.189Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-03-19 14:14 GMT+8] 看一下日志点评技能，这个技能不太好用，我要开始优化他"}],"timestamp":1773900856186}}
{"type":"message","id":"ba598557","parentId":"4b2c71d6","timestamp":"2026-03-19T06:14:19.873Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"用户让我查看日志点评技能，这个技能不太好用，需要优化。我需要先找到这个技能的位置，然后读取它。\n\n让我先搜索一下 session-logs 技能，因为用户提到的是\"日志点评\"。","thinkingSignature":"5f2c1233868505af9962d713a3652dcd9d01bd56fb98e8f49d80831399fab0a1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tpwpdhx6d69i_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/session-logs/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":52,"output":83,"cacheRead":35963,"cacheWrite":241,"totalTokens":36339,"cost":{"input":0.0000156,"output":0.0000996,"cacheRead":0.0010788899999999999,"cacheWrite":0.000028919999999999998,"total":0.0012230099999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773900856187}}
{"type":"message","id":"78bbd2aa","parentId":"ba598557","timestamp":"2026-03-19T06:14:19.894Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tpwpdhx6d69i_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: session-logs\ndescription: Search and analyze your own session logs (older/parent conversations) using jq.\nmetadata: { \"openclaw\": { \"emoji\": \"📜\", \"requires\": { \"bins\": [\"jq\", \"rg\"] } } }\n---\n\n# session-logs\n\nSearch your complete conversation history stored in session JSONL files. Use this when a user references older/parent conversations or asks what was said before.\n\n## Trigger\n\nUse this skill when the user asks about prior chats, parent conversations, or historical context that isn't in memory files.\n\n## Location\n\nSession logs live at: `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/` (use the `agent=<id>` value from the system prompt Runtime line).\n\n- **`sessions.json`** - Index mapping session keys to session IDs\n- **`<session-id>.jsonl`** - Full conversation transcript per session\n\n## Structure\n\nEach `.jsonl` file contains messages with:\n\n- `type`: \"session\" (metadata) or \"message\"\n- `timestamp`: ISO timestamp\n- `message.role`: \"user\", \"assistant\", or \"toolResult\"\n- `message.content[]`: Text, thinking, or tool calls (filter `type==\"text\"` for human-readable content)\n- `message.usage.cost.total`: Cost per response\n\n## Common Queries\n\n### List all sessions by date and size\n\n```bash\nfor f in ~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/*.jsonl; do\n  date=$(head -1 \"$f\" | jq -r '.timestamp' | cut -dT -f1)\n  size=$(ls -lh \"$f\" | awk '{print $5}')\n  echo \"$date $size $(basename $f)\"\ndone | sort -r\n```\n\n### Find sessions from a specific day\n\n```bash\nfor f in ~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/*.jsonl; do\n  head -1 \"$f\" | jq -r '.timestamp' | grep -q \"2026-01-06\" && echo \"$f\"\ndone\n```\n\n### Extract user messages from a session\n\n```bash\njq -r 'select(.message.role == \"user\") | .message.content[]? | select(.type == \"text\") | .text' <session>.jsonl\n```\n\n### Search for keyword in assistant responses\n\n```bash\njq -r 'select(.message.role == \"assistant\") | .message.content[]? | select(.type == \"text\") | .text' <session>.jsonl | rg -i \"keyword\"\n```\n\n### Get total cost for a session\n\n```bash\njq -s '[.[] | .message.usage.cost.total // 0] | add' <session>.jsonl\n```\n\n### Daily cost summary\n\n```bash\nfor f in ~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/*.jsonl; do\n  date=$(head -1 \"$f\" | jq -r '.timestamp' | cut -dT -f1)\n  cost=$(jq -s '[.[] | .message.usage.cost.total // 0] | add' \"$f\")\n  echo \"$date $cost\"\ndone | awk '{a[$1]+=$2} END {for(d in a) print d, \"$\"a[d]}' | sort -r\n```\n\n### Count messages and tokens in a session\n\n```bash\njq -s '{\n  messages: length,\n  user: [.[] | select(.message.role == \"user\")] | length,\n  assistant: [.[] | select(.message.role == \"assistant\")] | length,\n  first: .[0].timestamp,\n  last: .[-1].timestamp\n}' <session>.jsonl\n```\n\n### Tool usage breakdown\n\n```bash\njq -r '.message.content[]? | select(.type == \"toolCall\") | .name' <session>.jsonl | sort | uniq -c | sort -rn\n```\n\n### Search across ALL sessions for a phrase\n\n```bash\nrg -l \"phrase\" ~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/*.jsonl\n```\n\n## Tips\n\n- Sessions are append-only JSONL (one JSON object per line)\n- Large sessions can be several MB - use `head`/`tail` for sampling\n- The `sessions.json` index maps chat providers (discord, whatsapp, etc.) to session IDs\n- Deleted sessions have `.deleted.<timestamp>` suffix\n\n## Fast text-only hint (low noise)\n\n```bash\njq -r 'select(.type==\"message\") | .message.content[]? | select(.type==\"text\") | .text' ~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/<id>.jsonl | rg 'keyword'\n```\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773900859888}}
{"type":"message","id":"e5db58ea","parentId":"78bbd2aa","timestamp":"2026-03-19T06:14:46.183Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"我找到了 session-logs 技能。这是一个使用 jq 和 rg 来搜索和分析会话日志的技能。\n\n用户说这个技能\"不太好用\"，要开始优化它。让我分析一下这个技能的不足之处：\n\n1. **完全依赖命令行工具**：用户必须手动执行 jq/rg 命令，对于不熟悉命令行的人很不友好\n2. **没有自动化能力**：用户需要自己写命令，技能没有提供直接对话式查询能力\n3. **使用门槛高**：需要了解 jq 语法、JSONL 结构、文件路径等\n4. **没有对话式交互**：用户不能直接问\"上周花了多少钱\"这种自然语言问题\n\n这个技能本质上只是一个\"使用手册\"，告诉用户有哪些命令可用，但并没有真正帮用户解决问题。用户需要自己动手写命令。\n\n一个好的优化方向应该是：\n1. **对话式交互**：用户可以用自然语言提问，AI 自动生成并执行合适的查询命令\n2. **结果解读**：不仅返回原始数据，还要解读成人类可读的形式\n3. **自动命令生成**：AI 根据用户问题自动构造 jq 命令\n\n让我向用户反馈这个分析，然后我们可以一起优化这个技能。","thinkingSignature":"e62617f27f045e4e62ab70bbeda3272d647efcefea45cc3e240f108fb95eb7bd"},{"type":"text","text":"明白，您说的是 `session-logs` 技能。我看了下，这个技能本质上是**一个命令手册**——列出了一堆 jq/rg 命令供用户手动执行，但**没有真正帮您查日志**。\n\n**当前问题**：\n1. **纯手工**：用户得自己写命令，会 jq 语法才行\n2. **无对话能力**：无法直接问\"上周花了多少钱\"\"上次跟谁聊了\"\n3. **结果 raw 返回**：查完还是一堆 JSON，得自己解读\n\n**优化方向建议**：\n- 我直接帮您查，您说需求我执行命令+解读结果\n- 或者把这个技能升级成**对话式查询**：您问自然语言，我自动构造命令并返回可读答案\n\n您想怎么优化？🦞"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":1371,"output":392,"cacheRead":35963,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37726,"cost":{"input":0.00041129999999999997,"output":0.0004704,"cacheRead":0.0010788899999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00196059}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773900859893}}
